   <title>
      <phrase/>Point-in-Time Swift Rings Recovery</title>
    <para>In this scenario, everything is still running (lifecycle manager, control plane nodes, and
      compute nodes) but you want to restore your Swift rings to a previous state.</para>
    <note>
      <para>Freezer backs up and restores Swift rings only, not Swift data.</para>
   </note>
    
      <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Restore from a Swift backup</bridgehead>
      <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para>Log in to the first Swift Proxy (<literal>SWF-PRX[0]</literal>) node.</para>
         </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Become root: </para>
            <screen>sudo su</screen>
         </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Source the backup environment file:
          </para>
            <screen>source /home/stack/backup.osrc</screen>
         </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>List the jobs:
          </para>
            <screen>freezer-scheduler -c &lt;hostname&gt; job-list</screen>
         </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Get the id corresponding to the job <literal>HLM Default: Swift restore from
            Swift</literal>.</para>
         </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Launch the restore
          job:</para>
            <screen>freezer-scheduler -c &lt;hostname&gt; job-start -j &lt;job-id&gt;</screen>
         </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>This will take some time. While you wait you can follow the progress in the
            <literal>/var/log/freezer-agent/freezer-scheduler.log</literal> log file.</para>
         </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Log in to the lifecycle manager.</para>
         </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Stop the Swift service:
          </para>
            <screen>cd ~/scratch/ansible/next/hos/ansible
ansible-playbook -i hosts/verb_hosts swift-stop.yml</screen>
         </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Log back in to the first Swift Proxy (<literal>SWF-PRX[0]</literal>) node.</para>
         </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Copy the restored files
          </para>
            <screen>cp -pr /tmp/swift_builder_dir_restore/* /etc/swiftlm/builder_dir/</screen>
         </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Log back in to the lifecycle manager.</para>
         </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Reconfigure the Swift service:\
          </para>
            <screen>cd ~/scratch/ansible/next/hos/ansible
ansible-playbook -i hosts/verb_hosts swift-reconfigure.yml</screen>
         </listitem>
      </orderedlist>
   
    
      <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Restore from an SSH backup</bridgehead>
      <para>Follow the same procedure as for Swift in the section immediately preceding this one, but
        select the job <literal>HLM Default: Swift restore from SSH</literal>.</para>
   
  </section>
